  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Specific/directed therapy for endocarditis caused by slow-growing, fastidious Gram-negative bacilli",
        "HACEK group of organisms (HABCEK if Bartonella included). For Bartonella, see Endocarditis, Bartonella."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Haemophilus parainfluenzae",
        "Aggregatibacter actinomycetemcomitans (formerly Actinobacillus)",
        "Aggregatibacter aphrophilus (formerly Haemophilus)",
        "Cardiobacterium hominis",
        "Eikenella corrodens",
        "Kingella species",
        "Also, Bartonella sp.",
        "NOTE: Suggested treatment regimens are not predictably active vs Bartonella sp."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Ceftriaxone",
            "dose": "2 gm",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q24h",
            "connector": "OR"
          },
          {
            "drug": "Ciprofloxacin",
            "dose": "400 mg",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q12h"
          }
        ],
        "durationDetail": {
          "fixedDuration": "4 weeks"
        }
      }
    },
    {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Treat for 6 weeks if prosthetic valve infection."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Ampicillin-sulbactam",
            "dose": "3 gm",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q6h"
          }
        ],
        "durationDetail": {
          "fixedDuration": "4 weeks"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "condition": "if growth is sufficient to permit susceptibility testing",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Ampicillin",
            "dose": "2 gm",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q4h"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Levofloxacin",
            "dose": "750 mg",
            "route": "po/IV",
            "frequency": "q24h",
            "connector": "OR"
          },
          {
            "drug": "Moxifloxacin",
            "dose": "400 mg",
            "route": "po/IV",
            "frequency": "q24h"
          }
        ],
        "durationDetail": {
          "fixedDuration": "4 weeks"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "notes": "option for oral step-down in selected patients who have responded to IV therapy and are clinically stable, but clinical experience is limited",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Ciprofloxacin",
            "dose": "750 mg",
            "route": "po",
            "frequency": "q12h"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Comments"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Avoid combination therapy with gentamicin due to nephrotoxicity",
        "Guideline references for HACEK/HABCEK endocarditis:",
        "American Heart Assn (Circulation 132:1435, 2015).",
        "British Society for Antimicrobial Therapy (J Antimicrob Chemother 67:269, 2012)",
        "European Heart Journal 25: 267, 2004"
      ]
    }
  ]
